stepAnswer: Oblique triangles, when two sides and a $$non-included$$ angle (SSA) are given.
stepTitle: What type of triangle results in an ambiguous case?
choices: Right triangles, when two sides and one angle are given.
Oblique triangles, when two sides and a $$non-included$$ angle (SSA) are given.
Acute triangles, when two sides and one angle are given.
Obtuse triangles, when two angles and one side are given.
